stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> New: first envelope / ID entered
  New --> Pinned: TOFU — key pinned on first session<br/>(petname assigned locally, never from wire)
  Pinned --> Verified: safety numbers compared out-of-band<br/>(QR scan or 60-digit match)

  Pinned --> KeyChanged_Pinned: identity key or device record changed
  Verified --> KeyChanged_Verified: identity key or device record changed

  state KeyChanged_Pinned {
    [*] --> WarnProminent
    note right of WarnProminent
      Prominent warning (org policy may
      escalate to block). Wording is
      canonical per verification-ux.md —
      clients must not soften it.
    end note
  }

  state KeyChanged_Verified {
    [*] --> BlockSends
    note right of BlockSends
      Sends BLOCKED until re-verified.
      This is the property that defeats
      a fully malicious server pair.
    end note
  }

  KeyChanged_Pinned --> Pinned: user acknowledges (re-pin)
  KeyChanged_Verified --> Verified: re-verified via safety numbers
  KeyChanged_Verified --> Blocked: user rejects new key
  Pinned --> Blocked: user blocks
  Verified --> Blocked: user blocks
  Blocked --> [*]
